rdfs:label: country
IAO:0000115: A collective generic term that refers here to a wide variety of dependencies, areas of special sovereignty, uninhabited islands, and other entities in addition to the traditional countries or independent states.

rdfs:label: continent
IAO:0000115: One of the large, unbroken masses of land into which the Earth's surface is divided.

rdfs:label: ancestry category
IAO:0000115: population category defined using ancestry informative markers (AIMs) based on genetic/genomic data

rdfs:label: ancestry status
IAO:0000115: general characterisation of the ancestry of a population or individual

rdfs:label: European
IAO:0000115:
Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as
European, Caucasian, White or one of the sub-populations from this region (e.g Dutch). This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap CEU, FIN, GBR, IBS and TSI populations.

rdfs:label: Asian
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals that either self-report or have been described as Asian but there was not sufficient information to allow classification as East Asian, Central Asian, South Asian or South-East Asian.

rdfs:label: African
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals that either self-report or have been described as African, but there was not sufficient information to allow classification as African American, AfroCaribbean or Sub-Saharan African.

rdfs:label: Native American
IAO:0000115: Includes indigenous individuals of North, Central and South America, descended from the original human migration into the Americas from Siberia. We note that there does not appear to be a suitable reference population for this category and efforts are required to fill this gap.

rdfs:label: Hispanic or Latin American
IAO:0000115:
Includes individuals who either self-report or are described by authors as Hispanic, Latino, Latin American or one of the sub-populations
from this region. This category includes individuals with known admixture of primarily European, African and Native American ancestries, though some may have also a degree of Asian (e.g. Peru). We also note that the levels of admixture vary depending on the country, with Caribbean countries carrying higher levels of African admixture when compared to South American countries, for example. This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap CLM, MXL, PEL and PUR populations

rdfs:label: Greater Middle Eastern  (Middle Eastern, North African or Persian)
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals who self-report or were described by authors as Middle Eastern, North African, Persian or one of the subpopulations from this region (e.g. Saudi Arabian). We note there is heterogeneity in this category with different degrees of admixture as well as levels of genetic isolation. We note that there does not appear to be a suitable reference population for this category and efforts are required to fill this gap.

rdfs:label: African American or Afro-Caribbean
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as African American or Afro-Caribbean. This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap ACB or ASW populations. We note that there is likely to be significant admixture with European ancestry populations.

rdfs:label: Oceanian
IAO:0000115:
Includes individuals that either self-report or have been described by authors as
Oceanian or one of the sub-populations from this region (e.g. Native Hawaiian). We note that there does not appear to be a suitable reference population for this category and efforts are required to fill this gap.

rdfs:label: uncategorised population
IAO:0000115: a population for which specific ancestry information is known but that does not fall into any of the defined ancestry categories

rdfs:label: genetically isolated population
IAO:0000115: a population with increased genetic homogeneity and reduced genetic variation due to cultural or geographic isolation

rdfs:label: Aboriginal Australian
IAO:0000115:
Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as
Australian Aboriginal. These are expected to be descendents of early human migration into Australia from Eastern Asia and can be distinguished from other Asian populations by mtDNA and Y chromosome variation.

rdfs:label: undefined ancestry population
IAO:0000115: population for which insufficient information is available to allocate it to a specific ancestral group or which contain individuals from a range of known ancestry categories, eg American

rdfs:label: genetically isolated ancestry
IAO:0000115: Ancestry that is the result of cultural or geographic isolation. Generally characterised by increased genetic homogeneity and reduced genetic variation

rdfs:label: admixed ancestry
IAO:0000115: Ancestry which is an admixture of more than one defined ancestral population. The degree and type of admixture may vary within a population and the accuracy of classification requires well-defined reference samples

rdfs:label: South Asian
IAO:0000115:
Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as South Asian or one of the sub-populations from this region (e.g Asian Indian). This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap
BEB, GIH, ITU, PJL and STU populations.

rdfs:label: South East Asian
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as South East Asian or one of the sub-populations from this region (e.g Vietnamese). This category also includes includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes KHV population. We note that East Asian and South East Asian populations are often conflated. However, recent studies indicate a unique genetic background for South East Asian populations.

rdfs:label: East Asian
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as East Asian or one of the sub-populations from this region (e.g Chinese). This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region, for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap CDX, CHB, CHS and JPT populations.

rdfs:label: Central Asian
IAO:0000115: Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as Central Asian. We note that there does not appear to be a suitable reference population for this population and efforts are required to fill this gap.

rdfs:label: Sub-Saharan African
IAO:0000115:
Includes individuals who either self-report or have been described by authors as SubSaharan African or one of the subpopulations from this region (e.g. Yoruban).
This category also includes individuals who genetically cluster with reference populations from this region for example 1000 Genomes and/or HapMap ESN, LWK, GWD, MSL, MKK and YRI populations.
